This is the analysis of HealthSystem A provided Pharmacy Dispensing Data for:

  1. Hospital Pharmacies (4) | 75850 Records | Jan 1 2019 to July 30 2019
  2. Remote Mail Order (1) | 253833 Records | June 28, 2018 to June 27 2019

A third Dataset is used for mapping NDCs provided in these dispensing files to Industry Standard 11 Digit NDC numbers to identify specific medications

  1. NDC Map | 1814 Records

Analysis of combined Dispensing data

Within the combined Dataset, there were 329683 observed Prescription dispensing events. Totaling $96,904,208. Of the total revenue, $39,332,536 represents Specialty Medications and $57,571,672 represents Non-Specialty.
Other summary stats:

* Unique ordering Physicians 12847
* Unique dispensed NDCs 6411
* Average dispensed volume daily (Hospital Pharmacies) 363
* Average dispensed volume daily (Mail Order) 891

Top Drugs Prescribed by Quantity Dispensed

Across the Health Systems combined Pharmacy business lines, the top quantity Medications dispensed are primarily traditional non-specialy medications that are common high-turn inventory at typical Retail and Mail Order locations. With the exception of the Immunosuppressive TACROLIMUS, the majority are maintenace mediations for typical health conditions (i.e.High blood pressure, Asthma, High cholestrol and Diabetes). This is a contrast from evaluating the same data for the top Mediations dispensed by Revenue as shown below:

Top Drugs Prescribed by Revenue

As expected, the top Medications dispensed by Revenue are more heavily skewed toward Specialty Medications. A number of injectble inflammatory disease drugs and oral oncolytics dispensed at much lower volumes still represent significant costs and revenue for HealthSystem A. These drugs are generally are prescribed by Specialists seeking to monitor how their patients are doing on Therapy as well as ease and transparency in determining status of referrals. Higher cost medications raise the level of expecations for both patient and provider.
